canonical:
  title: 次珍原客館韻
  author: 楊熙止
  language: lzh
  text: 山藏小縣石田多村似朱陳八九家杜宇一聲愁欲死滿庭明月照梨花
  rtl: true
  vertical: true
lzh_formatted:
  title: 次珍原客館韻
  author: 楊熙止
  language: lzh
  text: 山藏小縣石田多。村似朱陳八九家。杜宇一聲愁欲死。滿庭明月照梨花。
korean:
  title: 차 진원 객관운
  author: 양희지
  language: kor
  text: |-
    뫼 속에 작은 고을 돌밭만 남아 있고
    마을은 주진촌 같아서 여덟 아홉 집
    접동새 한 소리에 시름 겨워 어이하리
    뜰에는 달빛 가득 배꽃에 비치누나
  url: https://db.itkc.or.kr/dir/item?itemId=BT#dir/node?dataId=ITKC_BT_1365A_1460_010_0020&viewSync=OT
  footnotes:
  - key: '[주-D001] 주진촌(朱陳村) : '
    value: 중국 서주(徐州)에 있는 마을로 주씨(朱氏) 진씨(陳氏) 두 성만이 사는 마을인데 지극히 화평하게 산다고 한다.
english:
  title: Matching the Rhyme of Jin Yuan's Guest Hall
  author: Yang Heezhi
  language: eng
  text: |-
    Among the mountains lies a small county, rocky fields stretched wide,
    A village like Zhuchen, just eight or nine homes side by side.
    One cry of the cuckoo—sorrow seizes my very soul,
    The courtyard flooded with moonlight, pear blossoms in its glow.
  footnotes:
    - Zhuchen Village was a legendary settlement in ancient China known for its peaceful coexistence, inhabited only by two clans who lived in perfect harmony—a fitting image for an idealized rural community.
